excerpt: Grand Dutch colonial administration building dating to the 1920s, now West Java's government house.
detail_description: Gedung Sate, located in Bandung, Indonesia, is a grand Dutch colonial administration building that has been repurposed as the government house of West Java. This historic complex once served as the headquarters for the Dutch Indies Government Companies and now houses the offices of the governor of West Java and the provincial house of representatives. The architecture is a captivating blend of Italianate Renaissance, Spanish Moorish, Balinese, and Thai influences.
name: Gedung Sate
address: Jl. Diponegoro No.22, Citarum, Bandung Wetan, Bandung City, West Java 40115, Indonesia

excerpt: Indoor-outdoor bamboo musical instrument workshop & craft center with live performances.
detail_description: Saung Angklung Udjo is a vibrant cultural hub that invites visitors to dive deep into the enchanting world of Sundanese music and art. This unique center, established in 1966, showcases the traditional bamboo instrument known as angklung through daily performances that captivate audiences with their melodious sounds. Guests can participate in interactive sessions to learn how to play this delightful instrument themselves, making it an engaging experience for all ages.
name: Saung Angklung Udjo
address: Jl. Padasuka No.118, Pasirlayung, Cibeunying Kidul, Bandung City, West Java 40192, Indonesia

excerpt: Family-focused indoor theme park with thrill rides, a theater & play areas for younger children.
detail_description: Trans Studio Bandung is an indoor theme park located within the Trans Studio Bandung Mall, making it a popular entertainment destination for families visiting the city. Divided into three zones - Magic Corner, Lost City, and Studio Central - the park offers a wide range of thrilling rides and attractions suitable for both children and adults. With over 20 different games to enjoy, including electric and water-based activities, kids can immerse themselves in a world of fun.
name: Trans Studio Bandung
address: Trans Studio Mall, Kecamatan Batununggal, Jl. Gatot Subroto No.289A, Cibangkong, Kota Bandung, Jawa Barat 40273, Indonesia

excerpt: Energetic shopping center offering brand-name stores, eateries, a cinema & other amusements.
detail_description: Paris Van Java Mall, located on Jalan Sukajadi Nomor 137-139, is a vibrant shopping center with a variety of brand-name stores, dining options, and entertainment. The mall features an open-air concept with numerous restaurants and cafes for visitors to enjoy. Inside the spacious mall, visitors can explore department stores, boutique shops, a grocery store, a cinema, a bookstore, as well as restaurants and coffee shops.
name: Paris Van Java
address: Jl. Sukajadi No.131-139, Cipedes, Sukajadi, Bandung City, West Java 40162, Indonesia

excerpt: Established zoo housing animals native to Indonesia's islands & from overseas, including elephants.
detail_description: Bandung Zoological Garden, located in the lively city of Bandung, Indonesia, is a popular tourist attraction for families and wildlife enthusiasts. Spanning 14 hectares, this captivating zoo is home to a diverse collection of animals from Indonesia and around the world. Visitors can enjoy exploring well-maintained enclosures that house native Indonesian wildlife as well as species from overseas. The zoo offers an enjoyable and educational experience for visitors of all ages.
name: Bandung Zoo (Kebun Binatang Bandung)
address: Jl. Kebun Binatang No.6, Lebak Siliwangi, Coblong, Bandung City, West Java 40132, Indonesia

excerpt: Theme park with European-style buildings, Dutch costumes for rent, a mini zoo & a hip restaurant.
detail_description: Farmhouse Susu Lembang is a charming artificial village that offers a unique European atmosphere, complete with picturesque replicas of famous European buildings and landmarks. Visitors can immerse themselves in the experience by renting traditional Dutch costumes for memorable photos. The village also features a mini zoo where families can interact with various animals, including feeding calves, sheep, rabbits, and even exotic creatures like hedgehogs and iguanas.
name: Farmhouse Susu Lembang
address: Jl. Raya Lembang No.108, Gudangkahuripan, Lembang, West Bandung Regency, West Java 40391, Indonesia

excerpt: Theme park dedicated to Africa & Asia with replica villages, a small zoo, food & souvenirs.
detail_description: The Great Asia Africa is a popular tourist destination in Bandung, offering a unique experience of exploring replicas of villages from Asia and Africa. Visitors can enjoy the sensation of traveling to different countries, including Japan, Korea, and Africa. The park features famous landmarks from various nations, allowing guests to immerse themselves in foreign cultures. Additionally, it boasts a small zoo and opportunities for shopping and dining on international cuisine.
name: The Great Asia Africa
address: Jl. Raya Lembang - Bandung No.71, Gudangkahuripan, Lembang, West Bandung Regency, West Java 40391, Indonesia

excerpt: Adventure park in a pine forest, with ATV riding, paintballing & imaginative props for selfies.
detail_description: Dago Dreampark is a popular adventure park located in a pine forest in Bandung. It has been one of the most visited places in the area for several years. The park, which opened in 2016, offers unique attractions that combine modernity, futuristic elements, and nature. Its design and architecture are inspired by the beauty of Bali's ecosystem while incorporating modern features. The park is known for activities such as ATV riding, paintballing, and imaginative props for taking selfies.
name: Dago Dreampark
address: Mekarwangi, Jl. Dago Giri No.Km. 2.2, Pagerwangi, Kec. Lembang, Kabupaten Bandung Barat, Jawa Barat 40135, Indonesia

excerpt: Synthetic grass covers this popular city square & meeting spot with views of the main mosque & city.
detail_description: Alun-Alun Bandung is a vibrant city square that serves as the heart of West Java's capital, offering a lively atmosphere for both locals and visitors. This urban hub is surrounded by significant landmarks, including the Great Mosque, which provides stunning panoramic views of the city from its tower. While exploring this historic area, you can also discover nearby attractions like the Asia Africa Monument and various museums that celebrate Bandung's rich cultural heritage.
name: Alun-Alun Bandung
address: Jl. Asia Afrika, Kebon Pisang, Regol, Bandung City, West Java, Indonesia

excerpt: Bandung, capital of Indonesia’s West Java province, is a large city set amid volcanoes and tea plantations. It's known for colonial and art deco architecture, a lively, university-town feel and – thanks to its 768m elevation – relatively cool tropical weather. Bandung is also a shopping destination, with fashion outlets clustered along Jalan Setiabudi and Jalan Riau in the Dago district.
detail_description: Bandung, the capital of Indonesia's West Java province, is a vibrant city known for its mix of colonial and art deco architecture. Situated amidst volcanoes and tea plantations, the city offers a lively university-town atmosphere and enjoys relatively cool tropical weather due to its elevated location. Bandung is also a popular shopping destination with numerous fashion outlets in districts like Dago.
name: Bandung
address: Bandung City, West Java, Indonesia

excerpt: Museum dedicated to the 1955 Bandung Conference of newly-independent African & Asian states.
detail_description: The Asian African Conference Museum is a historical site dedicated to the 1955 Bandung Conference, which brought together newly-independent African and Asian states. This significant event marked a milestone in world history by uniting 29 countries from both continents during a turbulent period of the Cold War. The museum, located at Gedung Merdeka where the conference took place, serves as a reminder of the principles outlined in the Bandung Declaration and aims to inspire global peace and cooperation.
name: Asia-Africa Conference Museum
address: Jl. Asia Afrika No.65, Braga, Sumurbandung, Bandung City, West Java 40111, Indonesia

detail_description: Cihampelas Walk Extension, located in the iconic city of Bandung, offers a stylish and captivating atmosphere that appeals to visitors. The interior design and overall ambiance are meticulously crafted, providing a visually appealing and comfortable environment. With a wide range of shops and eateries catering to different tastes, this mall has something for everyone. It's known for its affordable prices, diverse dining options, entertainment offerings, and relaxing ambiance.
name: Cihampelas Walk Extention
address: Jl. Cihampelas Walk No.1, Cipaganti, Kecamatan Coblong, Kota Bandung, Jawa Barat 40131, Indonesia

excerpt: Bustling landscaped park featuring boating, fountains, sculptures, gardens, concerts & more.
detail_description: Teras Cikapundung BBWS is a vibrant landscaped park that offers a variety of activities such as boating, fountains, sculptures, gardens, and concerts. Situated near the university, it has undergone a remarkable transformation from a polluted and neglected area to an inviting public space. Visitors can enjoy water sports on the Citarum river and take in scenic views of the city.
name: Teras Cikapundung BBWS
address: 4J84+7P9, Jl. Siliwangi, Hegarmanah, Cidadap, Bandung City, West Java 40131, Indonesia

detail_description: Located at Jalan Cibadak No. 50-155, Astana Anyar, the Cibadak Night Culinary Festival is like Bandung's version of 'Chinatown.' Operating from 7:00 AM to 2:00 AM daily, it offers a variety of delicious dishes inspired by Chinese culture, with most being non-halal.
name: Cibadak Night Culinary Festival
address: Jl. Cibadak No.50-155, Cibadak, Astanaanyar, Bandung City, West Java 40241, Indonesia

excerpt: Known for its unique architecture, this popular street is home to historic buildings, cafes & shops.
detail_description: Jl. Asia Afrika, also known as Asia Afrika Street, is a popular destination in Bandung with a rich historical significance. It is home to historic buildings, cafes, and shops that showcase unique architecture reminiscent of the old Dutch city. The street holds great importance as it was the site where Governor-General Herman Willem Deaendels ordered the establishment of Bandung.
name: Jl. Asia Afrika
address: Kota Bandung, Jawa Barat, Indonesia

excerpt: Outlet for clothes, shoes & bags, also featuring casual eateries with seating in a quaint garden.
detail_description: Rumah Mode Factory Outlet is a bustling shopping destination in Bandung, offering a wide range of clothing, shoes, and bags. The outlet also features cozy eateries set in a charming garden. It's known for its popularity and can get quite crowded on weekends. The complex includes various shops like Mode Plus, Natural, Donatello on Jl Setiabudi, as well as others like Blossom, Glamour, Raffles City on Jl Dago and more.
name: Rumah Mode Factory Outlet
address: Jl. Dr. Setiabudi No.41, Pasteur, Sukajadi, Bandung City, West Java 40161, Indonesia

excerpt: Fashionable market with stalls for Java-style fruit salad & fritters with outdoor seating.
detail_description: Paskal Food Market, located along Pasir Kaliki Road, is a trendy market offering a variety of Indonesian and international cuisine. The market features over 50 food stalls with more than 1100 menu options to choose from. Visitors can enjoy Java-style fruit salad, fritters, es cendol (iced sweet dessert), and roti bakar Bandung (grilled ham and cheese sandwich). At night, the market transforms into a lively hub with fairy lights and live music.
name: Paskal Food Market
address: Paskal Hyper Square, Jl. Pasir Kaliki No.25-27, Kebon Jeruk, Andir, Bandung City, West Java 40181, Indonesia

excerpt: Lively shopping center offering a department store, multiple floors of boutiques & casual eateries.
detail_description: Bandung Indah Plaza is a vibrant shopping center situated in the heart of Bandung on Merdeka Street. It's known for its department store, multiple floors of boutiques, casual eateries, and a large supermarket. The complex also features cinemas and numerous dining options. Connected to the Hyatt Regency Bandung Hotel, it offers a seamless blend of retail, dining, and entertainment experiences.
name: Bandung Indah Plaza
address: Jl. Merdeka No.56, Citarum, Bandung Wetan, Bandung City, West Java 40115, Indonesia

excerpt: Airy permanent tents in a relaxed resort offering a cafe, a petting zoo & a spa, plus outdoor pools.
detail_description: The Maribaya Natural Hot Spring Resort is a popular tourist attraction located in Bandung. The resort offers beautiful views of the cityscape and offers a variety of attractions that can be enjoyed by visitors. Popular features at the resort include the warm springs’ name, Curug Maribaya, which make it an interesting destination to visit. In addition, the resort has comfortable tents for easy camping as well as luxurious showers and bathrooms.
name: Maribaya Natural Hot Spring Resort
address: Jl. Maribaya No.105/212, Langensari, Lembang, West Bandung Regency, West Java 40391, Indonesia

detail_description: Trans Studio Mall Bandung is a modern and inviting shopping center that offers a wide range of retail outlets, including high-end stores selling fashion, electronics, and home goods. It also features various entertainment facilities such as cinemas, bowling alleys, billiards, and children's play areas. Additionally, the mall houses a large supermarket along with several restaurants and cafes for visitors to enjoy.
name: Trans Studio Mall Bandung
address: Jl. Gatot Subroto No.289, Cibangkong, Batununggal, Bandung City, West Java 40273, Indonesia
